00:14:51.265 --> 00:14:52.974
So what do we do?
Do we talk about dreams?

237
00:14:53.059 --> 00:14:54.517
What's next? What's the score?

238
00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:56.770
We'll talk about dreams. It's your nickel.

239
00:14:56.979 --> 00:15:00.273
Sure. I had another one about Debi.

240
00:15:00.566 --> 00:15:02.442
That girl you're obsessed with?

241
00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:04.402
Don't you think "obsessed"
is a strong word?

242
00:15:04.862 --> 00:15:08.531
Recurring dreams of loss and pain
for 10 years featuring the same person?

243
00:15:08.616 --> 00:15:12.577
Yeah. maybe it's a bit obsessive.

244
00:15:12.953 --> 00:15:16.289
I had one where I was
that television mechanical rabbit.

245
00:15:16.373 --> 00:15:19.167
- You know. with the...
- The battery bunny.

246
00:15:19.293 --> 00:15:20.627
Yeah. I was the bunny.

247
00:15:20.711 --> 00:15:22.712
That sounds like a very.
very depressed dream.

248
00:15:22.797 --> 00:15:24.380
- Really? Why?
- Yes.

249
00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:25.882
Martin. it's a terrible dream.

250
00:15:25.966 --> 00:15:28.176
It's depressing to
dream about that rabbit.

251
00:15:28.302 --> 00:15:30.845
It's got no brain. it's got no blood.
It's got no anima.

252
00:15:31.305 --> 00:15:34.432
It just keeps banging on those
meaningless cymbals endlessly.

253
00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:37.393
and going and going and going.

254
00:15:37.478 --> 00:15:40.188
- Time is up.
- Time's up already?

255
00:15:40.272 --> 00:15:42.315
You really wanna do half a session?

256
00:15:44.610 --> 00:15:47.237
Can we just pretend like we have
a normal doctor-patient relationship?

257
00:15:47.321 --> 00:15:50.156
I'll ask you a piece of advice.
you give me an answer.

258
00:15:50.241 --> 00:15:52.158
You know. advice.
Should I go to the reunion?

259
00:15:52.409 --> 00:15:55.203
- Yes. yes. get out of town.
- Thank you.

260
00:15:55.287 --> 00:15:57.622
Go see some old friends.
have some punch.

261
00:15:57.706 --> 00:15:59.290
- Visit with what's-her-name.
- Debi.

262
00:15:59.375 --> 00:16:01.709
Debi. Don't kill anybody for a few days.

263
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:03.461
- See what it feels like.
- Give it a shot.

264
00:16:03.546 --> 00:16:06.756
No. no. don't give it a shot.
Don't shoot anything.

265
00:16:12.555 --> 00:16:16.599
"Services for Detroit contract
terminated"?

266
00:16:16.684 --> 00:16:21.104
"Contract being serviced
by alternate vendor for original quote."

267
00:16:21.188 --> 00:16:23.648
What fucking alternate vendor?

268
00:16:23.732 --> 00:16:25.275
No. no. no.

269
00:16:25.359 --> 00:16:30.029
"Preparations have begun
in good faith."

270
00:16:33.826 --> 00:16:36.244
Fucking Martin Blank.

271
00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:39.205
Snaked the Detroit job from under me.

272
00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:49.632
Agent Farrell.

273
00:16:49.717 --> 00:16:53.261
Yes. extension 1715. please.

274
00:16:54.138 --> 00:16:56.014
- Yeah.
- Lardner?

275
00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:58.308
- Yeah.
- I've got your pigeon for you.

276
00:16:58.559 --> 00:17:00.351
Arriving Detroit Airport
today.

277
00:17:00.436 --> 00:17:02.312
He's supposed to hit
a star federal witness.

278
00:17:02.396 --> 00:17:05.899
Now. my advice is. you wait till he gets
the witness. and then you guys do him.

279
00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:12.322
When I'm out walkin'. I strut my stuff
and I'm so strung out

280
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:17.118
I'm high as a kite. I just might
stop to check you out

281
00:17:17.203 --> 00:17:21.915
Let me go on like I blister in the sun

282
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:27.462
Let me go on. big hands. I know
you're the one

283
00:17:28.589 --> 00:17:32.425
Remember to kick it over

284
00:17:32.509 --> 00:17:37.096
No one will guide you. Armagideon time

285
00:17:37.181 --> 00:17:38.806
You've never met
Martin Blank.

286
00:17:38.891 --> 00:17:40.642
Grocer pointed him
out to me.

287
00:17:40.809 --> 00:17:43.269
I'm telling you
that you never met Martin Blank. okay?

288
00:17:43.354 --> 00:17:46.773
No. 17 months ago. I was posting
a walk in Lisbon. and he was there.

289
00:17:46.857 --> 00:17:49.317
He hasn't been in Lisbon since 1990.

290
00:17:49.401 --> 00:17:51.527
You know how I know that?
I read the file.

291
00:17:51.779 --> 00:17:53.571
- Read the file.
- No. actually. as a matter of fact.

292
00:17:53.656 --> 00:17:56.241
I actually talked to him in Bonn.

293
00:17:56.867 --> 00:17:59.369
You always...
You always have to know everybody.

294
00:17:59.453 --> 00:18:01.204
Tell you what.
Why don't I take the weekend off

295
00:18:01.288 --> 00:18:03.081
and you kill him.
since you two are so close?

296
00:18:03.165 --> 00:18:04.707
All right. I'll do that.

297
00:18:04.792 --> 00:18:09.128
The battle is getting hotter

298
00:18:09.213 --> 00:18:14.008
In this iration. Armagideon time

299
00:18:14.093 --> 00:18:15.343
Hi. I'm Debi Newberry.

300
00:18:15.427 --> 00:18:19.847
This is WGPM FM. Grosse Pointe.
Window on the Pointes.

301
00:18:20.099 --> 00:18:23.101
You heard from Massive Attack.
Public Enemy. Morphine.

302
00:18:23.185 --> 00:18:27.897
that's my personal favorite.
and Duane Eddy's twangy guitar.

303
00:18:28.065 --> 00:18:29.691
Good to hear
Toots and the Maytals. huh?

304
00:18:30.317 --> 00:18:35.113
And as you know. this weekend is
Pointes High class of '86 reunion.

305
00:18:35.281 --> 00:18:36.990
So in honor of this momentous event.

306
00:18:37.074 --> 00:18:40.243
I'm making this an all-'80s.
all-vinyl weekend.

307
00:18:41.245 --> 00:18:43.705
Stay tuned to Window on the Pointes.
and I'll keep you posted

308
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:47.333
on all this reunion-related nonsense.

309
00:18:47.668 --> 00:18:50.753
Hey. I know everybody's coming back
to take stock of their lives.

310
00:18:50.838 --> 00:18:51.921
You know what I say?

311
00:18:52.339 --> 00:18:54.590
Leave your livestock alone.

312
00:18:54.675 --> 00:18:56.759
Kick back and relax. and ponder this.

313
00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:01.306
Where are all the good men dead?

314
00:19:01.390 --> 00:19:04.767
In the heart or in the head?

315
00:19:04.852 --> 00:19:06.686
So here's another cold cup of coffee
from The Clash.

316
00:19:17.448 --> 00:19:19.324
Sing. Michael. sing

317
00:19:19.950 --> 00:19:22.702
on the route of the 19 bus

318
00:19:25.456 --> 00:19:26.831
Welcome back. Pointers.

319
00:19:30.044 --> 00:19:32.462
Hear them sayin'

320
00:19:32.546 --> 00:19:34.547
How you get a rude and a reckless?

321
00:19:34.631 --> 00:19:37.133
Don't you be so crude and a feckless

322
00:19:37.217 --> 00:19:39.969
You been drinking brew for breakfast

323
00:19:40.054 --> 00:19:42.221
Rudie can't fail

324
00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:49.312
I went to the market to realize
my soul

325
00:19:49.396 --> 00:19:54.233
What I need. I just don't have

326
00:19:55.069 --> 00:19:59.655
First they curse. then they press me
till I hurt

327
00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:03.659
We say Rudie can't fail

328
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:06.662
Mrs. K. Mrs. Kinetta. it's Martin.

329
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:09.499
Martin. my God.

330
00:20:09.583 --> 00:20:11.209
- It's you.
- Hey.

331
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:12.543
Oh. God.

332
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:16.672
You've been Detroit's most famous
disappearing act since white flight.

333
00:20:16.757 --> 00:20:18.841
You look exactly the same. Mrs. K.

334
00:20:19.134 --> 00:20:22.011
- You look great is what I mean. Great.
- Thank you very much. Martin.

335
00:20:22.096 --> 00:20:23.971
You have always been
very good at saying that

336
00:20:24.056 --> 00:20:25.765
and not sounding like a kiss-ass.

337
00:20:26.141 --> 00:20:28.267
So what happened?

338
00:20:28.435 --> 00:20:31.354
I mean. we thought Princeton. Harvard.

339
00:20:31.522 --> 00:20:34.524
You fooled us all
in the teachers' pool and went nowhere.

340
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:36.317
I guess you could say I went west.
you know?

341
00:20:36.402 --> 00:20:38.945
The way of Horatio Alger.
Davy Crockett. the Donner party.

342
00:20:39.029 --> 00:20:42.031
Thank you. thank you.
That's a barrage of imagery.

343
00:20:42.116 --> 00:20:45.493
Are you still. you know. inflicting
all that horrible Ethan Frome damage?

344
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:47.286
- Is that off the curriculum?
- It's off.

345
00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:49.872
- That's a horrible book.
- That's a very nice tie you have on.

346
00:20:49.957 --> 00:20:52.125
You look like a mortician. I mean...

347
00:20:52.209 --> 00:20:53.251
- You like it?
- Yeah. thanks.

348
00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:54.836
You still got that
Mary Tyler Moore thing.

349
00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:56.796
Thank you. thank you. That's enough.

350
00:20:57.214 --> 00:20:58.798
- Good to see you again.
- Good to see you.

351
00:20:58.882 --> 00:21:01.300
- Where are you off to?
- I'm going home.

352
00:21:02.219 --> 00:21:03.302
Are you?

353
00:21:04.430 --> 00:21:07.640
- Gosh. well. they're playing my song.
- All right.

354
00:21:07.766 --> 00:21:10.560
- Take care. Martin.
- It was nice to see you again.

355
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:13.563
Mrs. K.

356
00:21:14.773 --> 00:21:20.278
When you were young
And your heart was an open book

357
00:21:21.155 --> 00:21:24.991
You used to say. "Live and let live"

358
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:28.286
You know you did. you know you did.
you know you did

359
00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:33.833
But if this ever-changing world
in which we live in

360
00:21:34.168 --> 00:21:38.671
Makes you give in and cry

361
00:21:41.633 --> 00:21:44.927
Say live and let die

362
00:21:48.932 --> 00:21:52.894
Live and let die

363
00:21:59.735 --> 00:22:01.027
- Here's your receipt.
- Thanks.

364
00:22:01.111 --> 00:22:03.070
- Have a nice day.
- You. too.

365
00:22:13.373 --> 00:22:15.458
What are you doing here?

366
00:22:15.542 --> 00:22:18.336
I'm doing a double shift.
What's it look like?

367
00:22:19.046 --> 00:22:20.922
How long have you worked here?

368
00:22:21.006 --> 00:22:22.381
- Couple of months.
- Yeah?

369
00:22:22.466 --> 00:22:24.550
Is there a manager here?
Do you have a supervisor?

370
00:22:24.635 --> 00:22:26.594
- No. but...
- How long have they worked here?

371
00:22:26.678 --> 00:22:29.889
- I'm not telling you.
- Yeah? Where do you live?

372
00:22:29.973 --> 00:22:32.850
- I'm not telling you that either.
- Where does your manager live?

373
00:22:32.935 --> 00:22:36.103
I used to... What...
What are you doing here?

374
00:22:36.188 --> 00:22:40.149
- What are... What are you doing here?
- I work here. I work here.

375
00:22:40.234 --> 00:22:41.817
And how long have you worked here?

376
00:22:41.902 --> 00:22:44.362
- Only a couple of months.
- All right. What's done is done.

377
00:22:44.446 --> 00:22:46.489
Just forget about the whole thing.

378
00:22:47.950 --> 00:22:50.243
- You all right. man?
- Sure.

379
00:22:51.662 --> 00:22:53.496
Sure.

380
00:22:58.585 --> 00:23:00.378
Hello. this is Dr. Oatman.

381
00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:03.798
If you'd like to leave a message.
I will get back to you shortly.

382
00:23:03.882 --> 00:23:06.425
Dr. Oatman. please pick up.
Pick up. It's Martin Blank.

383
00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:08.886
I'm standing where my living room was.

384
00:23:08.971 --> 00:23:12.306
and it's not here because the house
is gone. and it's an Ultimart.

385
00:23:13.308 --> 00:23:15.768
You can never go home again. Oatman.

386
00:23:16.395 --> 00:23:17.728
But I guess you can shop there.

387
00:23:18.772 --> 00:23:20.481
Pick up! I know you're there. Oatman.

388
00:23:25.779 --> 00:23:28.322
You got any ideas
how you want to wax this guy?

389
00:23:28.407 --> 00:23:30.157
Can't you just say kill?

390
00:23:30.242 --> 00:23:32.952
You always gotta romanticize it...
Go. Go. go. go.

391
00:23:37.749 --> 00:23:39.208
Marcella.

392
00:23:39.293 --> 00:23:41.460
Never mind that.
Find out where my mother is.

393
00:23:41.545 --> 00:23:43.421
I want my mom.

394
00:23:47.968 --> 00:23:50.595
Pardon me. do you know
where I might find Mary Blank?

395
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:52.597
She's over there.

396
00:23:54.141 --> 00:23:56.976
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

397
00:24:02.232 --> 00:24:04.775
There he is. Martin.

398
00:24:04.860 --> 00:24:06.444
Mom.

399
00:24:06.862 --> 00:24:08.529
Come have a seat over here.

400
00:24:09.323 --> 00:24:11.824
That's not very nice. but sit down. Yeah.

401
00:24:12.367 --> 00:24:14.243
They're fun.

402
00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:17.788
Hi. Martin.

403
00:24:18.332 --> 00:24:20.916
Why are you wearing black?

404
00:24:21.084 --> 00:24:24.378
So like a gangster.

405
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:30.217
So I spoke to your father the other day.

406
00:24:30.636 --> 00:24:34.180
- I imagine that'd be rather difficult.
- No. no. it wasn't. It wasn't.

407
00:24:34.348 --> 00:24:36.307
- No?
- No.

408
00:24:36.558 --> 00:24:39.518
They told me
you have been taking lithium.

409
00:24:39.811 --> 00:24:41.520
Yes. Those blabbermouths.

410
00:24:43.732 --> 00:24:47.151
We've had some laughs.
haven't we. Martin?

411
00:24:47.235 --> 00:24:48.653
Mmm-hmm.

412
00:24:48.737 --> 00:24:50.655
It's good to see you again.

413
00:24:52.616 --> 00:24:55.826
Mom. what happened to the house.
and all the money I sent?

414
00:24:55.994 --> 00:24:59.121
They stole. I don't do money.

415
00:24:59.373 --> 00:25:02.083
You know. time allows miracles.

416
00:25:02.250 --> 00:25:03.834
Time.

417
00:25:04.002 --> 00:25:06.420
- And you need time. that's all.
- Sir?

418
00:25:06.672 --> 00:25:09.382
Excuse me. It's time for her medication.

419
00:25:09.466 --> 00:25:11.717
Nurse Scott is my best friend.

420
00:25:12.052 --> 00:25:13.386
We met.

421
00:25:13.553 --> 00:25:15.054
- Okay.
- Okay.

422
00:25:16.848 --> 00:25:18.474
Oh. God. There's just so much here.

423
00:25:19.393 --> 00:25:21.560
You're gonna be okay. honey.

424
00:25:21.728 --> 00:25:22.895
Okay?

425
00:25:23.063 --> 00:25:24.689
Okay.

426
00:25:27.234 --> 00:25:29.402
What's happening?

427
00:25:34.574 --> 00:25:36.283
Mom?

428
00:25:36.576 --> 00:25:38.202
Yes?

429
00:25:39.496 --> 00:25:43.624
You are a handsome devil.
What's your name?

430
00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:46.293
Martin.

431
00:25:46.378 --> 00:25:48.421
Martin. right.

432
00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:53.592
"So the colonel's lady like Judy O'Grady.

433
00:25:53.760 --> 00:25:55.970
"Are twins under the skin"

434
00:25:56.138 --> 00:25:58.013
Oh. silly.

435
00:26:01.184 --> 00:26:05.062
I say somebody

436
00:26:10.444 --> 00:26:14.947
Will find a way out of here

437
00:26:18.952 --> 00:26:23.789
Here's hopin' somebody

438
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:30.629
Can find a way out of here

439
00:27:05.165 --> 00:27:06.916
Martin's back.

440
00:27:14.716 --> 00:27:16.383
Hey. I'm Debi Newberry.

441
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:19.637
and stand by your phones. because
any time now. I'll be giving away tickets

442
00:27:19.721 --> 00:27:22.807
to see Palace this Saturday night
in concert at Cobo Hall.

443
00:27:23.183 --> 00:27:24.266
You can call in for tickets

444
00:27:24.351 --> 00:27:26.477
or just show up at Cobo Hall
and say my name.

445
00:27:26.728 --> 00:27:28.771
No. I'm just kidding.

446
00:27:30.732 --> 00:27:32.525
Hi.

447
00:27:35.737 --> 00:27:36.737
Uh...

448
00:27:37.364 --> 00:27:40.533
And here's The Specials.

449
00:27:40.700 --> 00:27:44.286
doing one of their songs.

450
00:27:49.918 --> 00:27:51.085
It's Martin.

451
00:27:51.670 --> 00:27:54.088
I know who you are.

452
00:27:54.172 --> 00:27:55.256
You're not dead.

453
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:58.968
- Hi.
- Hi. Shake my hand.

454
00:27:59.052 --> 00:28:00.803
How are you?

455
00:28:01.847 --> 00:28:03.347
Wow.

456
00:28:21.074 --> 00:28:22.908
How... How are you?
It's good to see you.

457
00:28:22.993 --> 00:28:25.536
You look great. How long has it been?
Ten years?

458
00:28:25.620 --> 00:28:26.912
How long has it been?

459
00:28:27.080 --> 00:28:30.165
Since you stood me up on prom night
and vanished without a word?

460
00:28:30.250 --> 00:28:32.626
Yeah. 10 years I think.

461
00:28:32.794 --> 00:28:34.128
Yeah.

462
00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:38.257
You tell me about yourself.

463
00:28:38.758 --> 00:28:43.387
In California. travel a lot
around on business.

464
00:28:43.763 --> 00:28:44.889
- That's it?
- Yeah.

465
00:28:45.056 --> 00:28:46.849
That's 10 years?

466
00:28:47.601 --> 00:28:48.893
Yeah.

467
00:28:48.977 --> 00:28:51.437
I would hope for a great abduction story
or something.

468
00:28:51.605 --> 00:28:53.856
I've had a few thrilling moments
here and there.

469
00:28:53.940 --> 00:28:56.317
but. you know. it flew by.

470
00:28:57.402 --> 00:28:59.111
So. what's your business?

471
00:29:00.155 --> 00:29:01.322
Professional killer.

472
00:29:02.657 --> 00:29:05.743
- Do you get dental with that?
- No.

473
00:29:08.955 --> 00:29:12.833
I gotta go. So you're working?
It's a great... I mean. it's a great show.

474
00:29:13.001 --> 00:29:15.461
I've been listening.
I mean. since I got back into town.

475
00:29:16.004 --> 00:29:18.631
- But I'll come back.
- What are the odds?

476
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:21.675
Very funny. I'll see you.

477
00:29:35.190 --> 00:29:38.150
Someone has
come to me out of the past

478
00:29:38.234 --> 00:29:40.694
reviving a feeling long since forgotten.

479
00:29:41.696 --> 00:29:45.991
I know I should be mad. and I am.

480
00:29:48.828 --> 00:29:51.872
- What's he doing?
- No clue.

481
00:29:53.416 --> 00:29:58.003
He says cryptic things
and is gone abruptly again.

482
00:30:02.550 --> 00:30:05.886
Oh. boy. What...
What is this I'm feeling here?

483
00:30:05.971 --> 00:30:09.098
Is this pain? Is this panic?
Is it pleasure?

484
00:30:09.182 --> 00:30:12.101
- Am I hungry? Who's hungry?
- Seventy-nine point five.

485
00:30:12.185 --> 00:30:13.894
Okay. the first five callers will receive

486
00:30:13.979 --> 00:30:16.605
a sentimental breakfast
from CuppaJoe's.

487
00:30:16.690 --> 00:30:20.192
courtesy of the long-lost love of my life.

488
00:30:22.195 --> 00:30:23.696
The man who vanished.

489
00:30:27.575 --> 00:30:31.036
The man who is walking
right back into the station

490
00:30:31.663 --> 00:30:33.747
and into my booth.

491
00:30:37.711 --> 00:30:39.336
Sit.

492
00:30:50.724 --> 00:30:54.768
Okay. let's take a random day.
Spring of '86.

493
00:30:56.813 --> 00:30:57.855
Two young lovers
with natural chemistry.

494
00:30:57.939 --> 00:30:59.982
- I'm on the air?
- Yeah.

495
00:31:01.067 --> 00:31:07.072
A girl sits in a $700 prom dress

496
00:31:07.949 --> 00:31:08.991
on the steps of her house.

497
00:31:09.075 --> 00:31:11.035
waiting for the most
romantic night of her young life.

498
00:31:12.120 --> 00:31:15.873
The boy never shows up. not until now.

499
00:31:16.041 --> 00:31:18.000
So. what's the question?

500
00:31:19.794 --> 00:31:20.836
Where have I been?

501
00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:22.212
More like.
"What happened. Mr. Blank?"

502
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:24.173
I don't know. I could venture a guess.

503
00:31:24.257 --> 00:31:26.717
but it would sound like
a rationalization. a cop-out.

504
00:31:27.135 --> 00:31:29.219
I thought coming home.
seeing some friends.

505
00:31:29.554 --> 00:31:31.221
and I thought maybe seeing you.
of course.

506
00:31:31.306 --> 00:31:33.932
would be the most important
part of that equation.

507
00:31:34.267 --> 00:31:37.478
That didn't... That didn't come out right.
This... This isn't even my idea.

508
00:31:37.771 --> 00:31:40.272
This whole thing
is my therapist's idea. really.

509
00:31:43.610 --> 00:31:45.736
Is this bothering...

510
00:31:56.456 --> 00:32:00.751
Okay. so you're back a decade late.

511
00:32:00.835 --> 00:32:03.045
and you're on some sort of
therapeutic assignment.

512
00:32:03.129 --> 00:32:05.380
and you wanna sort things out with me.

513
00:32:05.465 --> 00:32:08.217
So the question now becomes
do I allow you access to me.

514
00:32:08.301 --> 00:32:11.804
- or do I call security?
- I don't think that'd be a good idea.

515
00:32:11.971 --> 00:32:15.182
Grosse Pointe. I need your help.
555-WGPM.

516
00:32:15.266 --> 00:32:17.267
Do you think maybe we could
get a cup of coffee.

517
00:32:17.352 --> 00:32:19.645
and I could try to explain or apologize?

518
00:32:22.357 --> 00:32:26.235
Come on. Marty. this segues
so nicely into my '80s weekend.

519
00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:30.405
Should a once-brokenhearted girl
give a guy a second chance?

520
00:32:31.658 --> 00:32:33.617
Let's go to the phones.

521
00:32:33.701 --> 00:32:34.910
You're on the air.

522
00:32:34.994 --> 00:32:37.079
- Hi. Debi. it's Gail.
- Oh. hi. Gail.

523
00:32:37.163 --> 00:32:38.747
You know. I wouldn't take him back yet.

524
00:32:38.832 --> 00:32:42.584
I'd make him jump through some hoops
for a while. walk over hot coals.

525
00:32:42.669 --> 00:32:45.963
- Make him beg for it.
- Harsh. That's very harsh. Gail.

526
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:48.841
Do you think maybe we could
discuss this in a more discreet setting?

527
00:32:49.008 --> 00:32:50.884
...beg like a beggar.
You know. come on.

528
00:32:51.845 --> 00:32:53.262
Next caller. you're on the air.

529
00:32:53.346 --> 00:32:56.765
Debi. man. it's Nathaniel.
I don't hear any real remorse.

530
00:32:56.850 --> 00:32:59.351
I mean. I don't think I'd let
this guy back in your life.

531
00:32:59.477 --> 00:33:02.062
And. dude. I'd make him
wear that prom dress.

532
00:33:02.564 --> 00:33:04.439
Does anybody else
have a question for Marty?

533
00:33:04.566 --> 00:33:06.942
- I do. but he's a shifty one.
- Put that down.

534
00:33:07.026 --> 00:33:10.737
I have a question for Marty.

535
00:33:11.364 --> 00:33:13.824
- Next caller. you're on the air.
- Yeah. Debi. hi.

536
00:33:13.908 --> 00:33:16.535
Long-time listener. first-time caller.
I love the show.

537
00:33:16.995 --> 00:33:18.829
So. Martin. what. no yellow ribbons?

538
00:33:19.038 --> 00:33:20.455
Didn't anybody miss you?

539
00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:23.500
Don't you think you should tell her
why you're really in town. tough guy?

540
00:33:23.585 --> 00:33:26.545
You know what we love?
We love tough guys like you.

541
00:33:27.213 --> 00:33:30.674
Thanks. That was our own Michigan
Militia. with their latest chart topper.

542
00:33:30.758 --> 00:33:33.468
Come on. people.
do I give this guy the time of day?

543
00:33:34.220 --> 00:33:38.140
Marty. do you have any
deeply personal responses

544
00:33:38.224 --> 00:33:40.184
- you wanna share with our listeners?
- No.

545
00:33:40.268 --> 00:33:41.894
Okay. he's shaking his head no.

546
00:33:41.978 --> 00:33:44.229
In radio. that usually signals
the end of the interview.

547
00:33:44.314 --> 00:33:46.857
Grosse Pointe. Michigan.
I hear you loud and clear.

548
00:33:46.941 --> 00:33:49.109
If you love something. set it free.

549
00:33:49.235 --> 00:33:53.614
If it comes back to you. it's. well.

550
00:33:56.075 --> 00:33:57.743
broken.

551
00:34:01.789 --> 00:34:04.750
Damn it. Never trust my instincts.

552
00:34:32.111 --> 00:34:33.946
Marty.

553
00:34:36.824 --> 00:34:38.242
Paul.

554
00:34:38.409 --> 00:34:40.827
- Don't leave me hanging. baby.
- Hey. man.

555
00:34:40.995 --> 00:34:43.080
How the hell you doing?

556
00:34:44.791 --> 00:34:47.042
Hey. Look at you.

557
00:34:47.126 --> 00:34:48.543
- Walk with me. man.
- Sure.

558
00:34:48.628 --> 00:34:50.587
- I got my car parked around the corner.
- Okay.

559
00:34:50.672 --> 00:34:55.133
Yeah. Goddamn. I worried
you joined a cult or something. man.

560
00:34:55.218 --> 00:34:56.593
Half expected you to
come back into town

561
00:34:56.678 --> 00:34:58.387
in a fennel wreath and paper pants.

562
00:34:58.471 --> 00:35:00.222
- No money in it.
- Says you.

563
00:35:00.306 --> 00:35:03.475
- Look at you. You've gone respectable.
- I stopped pouting on the sidelines.

564
00:35:03.559 --> 00:35:05.727
I got in the game.
joined the working week.

565
00:35:05.812 --> 00:35:07.938
So why don't you valet park
your high horse. slick.

566
00:35:08.022 --> 00:35:10.399
- and take it easy on your buddy?
- It was a cheap shot.

567
00:35:10.483 --> 00:35:12.150
Yeah. it was.

568
00:35:13.194 --> 00:35:15.612
- Man. let's catch up. huh?
- Yeah. let's catch up.

569
00:35:15.697 --> 00:35:19.241
I got a real estate deal. I'm taking them
through a final walkthrough. you know.

570
00:35:19.784 --> 00:35:21.076
- This your Beemer?
- Yeah.

571
00:35:21.160 --> 00:35:22.244
In Detroit? That's sacrilege.

572
00:35:22.328 --> 00:35:24.079
Well. you know. guess who I got it from?

573
00:35:24.163 --> 00:35:26.957
- I have no idea.
- Bob Destepello.

574
00:35:27.041 --> 00:35:29.251
- Bob Destepello sold you a car?
- Yeah. he did.

575
00:35:29.335 --> 00:35:31.962
Didn't he break your collarbone
and steal your woman?

576
00:35:32.046 --> 00:35:33.755
- Yeah.
- So you're in real estate. huh?

577
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:36.758
Yeah. I got a couple of newlyweds
with a decision-making disorder.

578
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:39.845
I'll just hold their hands
and reinforce their clarity.

579
00:35:40.013 --> 00:35:42.681
Isn't there some sort of Frank Lloyd
Wright connection with this?

580
00:35:42.765 --> 00:35:45.600
You know what? There is indeed.
For the life of me. I can't...

581
00:35:45.685 --> 00:35:47.352
Blank!

582
00:35:53.026 --> 00:35:54.943
Hey. Blank.

583
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:56.778
I was driving by. I saw you on the lawn.

584
00:35:56.863 --> 00:35:59.781
I thought there was gonna be a problem
at first. before I recognized you.

585
00:36:00.366 --> 00:36:02.242
Terry Rostand. How you doing? PHS.

586
00:36:02.368 --> 00:36:04.536
Terry Rostand. Oh. yeah.
you were always the guy who was...

587
00:36:04.662 --> 00:36:06.788
- Yeah. I remember you.
- Yeah. '86.

588
00:36:06.873 --> 00:36:08.957
How you doing. man? You look good.
You became a cop.

589
00:36:09.042 --> 00:36:11.626
- Nice badge.
- No. no. no. I'm not a peace officer.

590
00:36:11.711 --> 00:36:13.128
This badge isn't
a meaningful symbol or anything.

591
00:36:13.212 --> 00:36:14.963
It's a badge of my company.

592
00:36:15.048 --> 00:36:17.841
We don't enforce the law. we execute
company policy for homeowners.

593
00:36:17.925 --> 00:36:20.510
- I get it. Cool. Cool.
- Yeah.

594
00:36:20.595 --> 00:36:23.305
- You mind talking a little shop?
- Sure.

595
00:36:23.389 --> 00:36:25.349
When are you authorized
to use deadly force?

596
00:36:25.433 --> 00:36:26.850
Well. you know. of course.

597
00:36:26.934 --> 00:36:29.311
taxes provide your basic service.
police and whatnot.

598
00:36:29.395 --> 00:36:31.146
but our customers
need a bit more than that.

599
00:36:31.230 --> 00:36:34.232
So if we find you on the property.
you know. we do what we have to do.

600
00:36:34.317 --> 00:36:37.235
So if I just look suspicious
on your customer's property

601
00:36:37.362 --> 00:36:39.696
under those. you know.
heightened circumstances.

602
00:36:39.781 --> 00:36:41.865
you have the authority to shoot me?

603
00:36:41.949 --> 00:36:43.200
Correct.

604
00:36:43.284 --> 00:36:45.410
Wow. All right. all right.
How'd you get the gig?

605
00:36:45.495 --> 00:36:47.371
You know. they were hiring.

606
00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:49.831
- It was only a two-week course.
- Yeah. that's good.

607
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:50.999
- You look good.
- Yeah. thanks.

608
00:36:51.084 --> 00:36:53.126
It's a beauty. What more can I say?

609
00:36:53.252 --> 00:36:55.212
You know. you'll be raising your family
in a work of art.

610
00:36:55.296 --> 00:36:57.172
A work of art in a work of art.

611
00:36:57.256 --> 00:36:59.257
Yeah.

612
00:36:59.926 --> 00:37:01.259
Well...

613
00:37:01.344 --> 00:37:03.428
I've always felt very temporary
about myself.

614
00:37:03.596 --> 00:37:06.431
and looking at the two of you
in this house.

615
00:37:06.599 --> 00:37:08.100
when my time comes. if it ever does.

616
00:37:08.267 --> 00:37:10.811
I want a house like this.
I want a wife like you.

617
00:37:13.606 --> 00:37:16.650
- And you'll be safe here.
- We really gotta go.

618
00:37:16.818 --> 00:37:19.569
Okay. give me a call. you guys.

619
00:37:19.654 --> 00:37:21.363
You're not gonna go through
another broker. are you?

620
00:37:21.447 --> 00:37:23.281
Definitely not.

621
00:37:23.449 --> 00:37:26.201
Cute couple.
I don't think they're buyers though.

622
00:37:26.285 --> 00:37:28.537
I don't know if you're qualified
to make that statement.

623
00:37:28.621 --> 00:37:30.872
From 11:00 to 3:00
I show the house. Terry.

624
00:37:30.957 --> 00:37:32.874
They don't look like people
who'd use the. you know...

625
00:37:32.959 --> 00:37:34.126
Did you get a call. Terry?

626
00:37:34.335 --> 00:37:36.837
No. I was just driving by.
and. you know.

627
00:37:36.921 --> 00:37:38.463
I saw some people milling
around the lawn here.

628
00:37:38.589 --> 00:37:40.715
No. there was just me. I was right there.

629
00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:42.759
Okay. that's what I thought.
I just came by.

630
00:37:42.844 --> 00:37:45.804
I show people houses here.
and I'd appreciate if you don't show up.

631
00:37:45.888 --> 00:37:48.598
I know. but you're coming around
in the neighborhood unannounced...

632
00:37:48.683 --> 00:37:51.393
- Did you get a call?
- No. but you don't know the alarm code.

633
00:37:51.477 --> 00:37:53.103
- Did you get a call?
- No. they go off.

634
00:37:53.187 --> 00:37:55.480
Okay. you're gonna have to go.

635
00:37:55.565 --> 00:37:57.232
I'm more a part of this
neighborhood than you are.

636
00:37:57.316 --> 00:37:58.483
And besides. a lot of times

637
00:37:58.568 --> 00:38:00.902
you don't know the alarm codes
when you're checking.

638
00:38:01.112 --> 00:38:02.988
- and the alarm goes off.
- Wow.

639
00:38:03.156 --> 00:38:05.157
Yeah. Yeah. for sure.

640
00:38:10.329 --> 00:38:12.747
Well. I'm sorry about
the temporary thing...

641
00:38:12.832 --> 00:38:14.749
No. don't worry about it. I don't even...

642
00:38:14.834 --> 00:38:16.585
Listen. I don't usually pimp my friends.

643
00:38:16.669 --> 00:38:19.629
but I got an excellent piece of property
you might want to look at.

644
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:21.965
- I got a few minutes.
- I gotta get something off my chest.

645
00:38:22.049 --> 00:38:25.343
- Have you been to see the old house?
- Yeah. They tore it down

646
00:38:25.511 --> 00:38:28.763
- in the name of convenience.
- Yeah. I brokered the deal.

647
00:38:28.848 --> 00:38:32.476
I tried to get a family in there.
but Ultimart made the best offer.

648
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.603
Well. thank you for profiting
on my childhood.

649
00:38:35.855 --> 00:38:39.065
Stop your fooling around

650
00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:41.943
Time you straighten right out

651
00:38:44.906 --> 00:38:47.908
Take a look at this new listing.

652
00:38:48.284 --> 00:38:51.786
- Debi's house.
- Yeah. kind of crept up on you. didn't it?

653
00:38:51.871 --> 00:38:54.372
No. you drove us here.

654
00:38:54.540 --> 00:38:56.082
Yeah.

655
00:39:06.552 --> 00:39:09.137
So how's the family. man?

656
00:39:09.222 --> 00:39:12.307
You don't know?
Of course you don't know.

657
00:39:12.391 --> 00:39:14.809
- Yeah. my parents are divorced.
- They got divorced?

658
00:39:14.894 --> 00:39:16.811
Yeah. my dad's shacking up
with this woman.

659
00:39:16.896 --> 00:39:18.230
She's 20 years younger than him.

660
00:39:18.314 --> 00:39:20.273
She's like a biscuit older than me.
It's ugly.

661
00:39:20.358 --> 00:39:22.150
My mom's making ceramic night-lights.

662
00:39:22.235 --> 00:39:24.277
Takes. like. the plain shells
and paints them...

663
00:39:24.362 --> 00:39:26.655
How's your sister?
Did she ever marry that guy. Kenny?

664
00:39:26.739 --> 00:39:29.991
- Kenny?
- Yeah. did that ever work out?

665
00:39:30.076 --> 00:39:32.494
Come on. man.
he did three years at Joliet.

666
00:39:32.578 --> 00:39:35.580
They put one of those bracelets on him.
like a LoJack. you know?

667
00:39:35.665 --> 00:39:38.166
They know where he is at all times.
I think he's at Pizza Hut now.

668
00:39:38.251 --> 00:39:39.793
- So let's not go there.
- No.

669
00:39:39.877 --> 00:39:42.295
Yeah. yeah.
So you look good. you seem good.

670
00:39:42.421 --> 00:39:44.089
Thank you. You may have...

671
00:39:45.091 --> 00:39:47.926
Ten years. man! Ten!

672
00:39:48.511 --> 00:39:51.179
Where have you been for 10 years?

673
00:39:51.556 --> 00:39:53.557
I freaked out.

674
00:39:54.141 --> 00:39:55.600
joined the Army.

675
00:39:55.768 --> 00:39:57.602
went into business for myself.

676
00:39:57.770 --> 00:39:59.771
I'm a professional killer.

677
00:40:00.231 --> 00:40:02.440
Does that... Do you have to do
postgraduate work for that.

678
00:40:02.525 --> 00:40:04.734
or can you jump right in?
I'm curious about that.

679
00:40:04.860 --> 00:40:07.779
- No. it's not. It's an open market.
- Open market? That's good.

680
00:40:08.489 --> 00:40:12.409
Ten years. man! Ten... Ten years!

681
00:40:12.577 --> 00:40:14.661
Ten years! Ten!

682
00:40:14.829 --> 00:40:18.290
Ten years! Ten years!

683
00:40:18.457 --> 00:40:21.960
I freaked out. I joined the Army.

684
00:40:22.086 --> 00:40:24.421
I worked for the government.
I went into business with myself.

685
00:40:24.505 --> 00:40:26.756
I'm a professional killer.
That's what I did!

686
00:40:27.425 --> 00:40:30.010
- Okay. well. can I join up?
- Yes!

687
00:40:34.098 --> 00:40:35.682
Come on.

688
00:40:35.850 --> 00:40:38.893
What about... How's your mom. man?
Is she still a little bit loopy?

689
00:40:38.978 --> 00:40:40.979
She's uncorked. man.

690
00:40:41.939 --> 00:40:43.148
All right. see you at

691
00:40:43.232 --> 00:40:45.609
the I've-peaked-and-I'm-kidding-myself
party.

692
00:41:05.046 --> 00:41:06.880
Pacific Trident Global.

693
00:41:06.964 --> 00:41:08.632
- I need some data.
- Hey. there.

694
00:41:08.716 --> 00:41:10.258
How'd the assignment go?

695
00:41:10.343 --> 00:41:12.177
I'll do it tomorrow.

696
00:41:13.554 --> 00:41:14.804
What's it look like?

697
00:41:15.014 --> 00:41:16.556
Looks fine.

698
00:41:16.724 --> 00:41:18.642
Like it always does.
nothing remarkable about it.

699
00:41:18.726 --> 00:41:20.518
Nothing remarkable at all.

700
00:41:20.853 --> 00:41:22.604
You're taking your time?

701
00:41:22.688 --> 00:41:24.230
Just being a professional?

702
00:41:24.565 --> 00:41:25.857
Something like that.

703
00:41:25.941 --> 00:41:28.068
Look. I got a job to do.
I'm gonna do it. right?

704
00:41:28.152 --> 00:41:32.113
The reason I called. Could you
find out who else is in town and why?

705
00:41:32.198 --> 00:41:34.282
I've made two spooks
and a ghoul so far.

706
00:41:34.367 --> 00:41:37.118
So if they've double-booked the job
and/or they're gonna kill me.

707
00:41:37.203 --> 00:41:39.829
I'd like to know about it.
That'd be great if you could find out.

708
00:41:40.039 --> 00:41:41.873
- Okay. got it.
- Bye-bye.

709
00:41:42.041 --> 00:41:44.209
Amelia? Wait. hold on a second.

710
00:41:44.377 --> 00:41:46.044
Pacific Trident Global.

711
00:41:46.212 --> 00:41:47.337
Janice?

712
00:41:49.674 --> 00:41:53.343
Yeah. no. where the fuck is it?
I ordered it three days ago.

713
00:41:57.765 --> 00:41:59.474
No. that doesn't work.

714
00:41:59.558 --> 00:42:02.644
That's... That's not right.
Let me go over it again. all right?

715
00:42:02.728 --> 00:42:06.523
Let's see. 3.000 rounds
of 9-mm subsonic.

716
00:42:06.607 --> 00:42:10.819
You had that.
I gave that to you on the fucking list.

717
00:42:11.570 --> 00:42:16.074
Well. I don't give a goddamn where it is.
you get it here now.

718
00:42:17.910 --> 00:42:19.035
Amelia?

719
00:42:19.120 --> 00:42:21.204
I'm sorry.

720
00:42:21.288 --> 00:42:22.664
Yeah. no.

721
00:42:22.748 --> 00:42:26.126
No. I'm... It's not gonna be
a boring soup. That's just the base.

722
00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:28.545
You put the chicken in.
you've got to add other flavors.

723
00:42:28.629 --> 00:42:31.131
Carrots and celery
are just a base of a soup.

724
00:44:03.015 --> 00:44:05.099
What the fuck. man?

725
00:44:37.842 --> 00:44:38.925
Cool.

726
00:44:39.385 --> 00:44:41.678
What'd you do that for?

727
00:44:42.388 --> 00:44:44.264
It's not me.

728
00:44:45.099 --> 00:44:46.641
You all right?

729
00:44:46.725 --> 00:44:48.810
No. I'm not all right.

730
00:44:48.894 --> 00:44:50.270
Take it easy.

731
00:44:50.354 --> 00:44:53.898
I'm hurt and pissed.
Gotta find a new job.

732
00:45:08.455 --> 00:45:10.832
- WGPM FM.
- Deborah. it's Martin.

733
00:45:10.916 --> 00:45:12.125
Hi. Martin.

734
00:45:12.209 --> 00:45:13.585
Listen. that thing didn't go as I planned.

735
00:45:13.669 --> 00:45:17.171
- Seeing you. it didn't go as I planned.
- It was just as I planned.

736
00:45:17.256 --> 00:45:18.506
I'm wondering how you are

737
00:45:18.591 --> 00:45:21.050
and I'd like to catch up with you.
I don't know if it's possible.

738
00:45:22.094 --> 00:45:23.428
Well. okay. let's catch up.

739
00:45:23.804 --> 00:45:26.514
Well. I thought maybe we could go
someplace and talk. and...

740
00:45:26.599 --> 00:45:29.517
- Well. I talk all day.
- Well. then just listen. Maybe...

741
00:45:29.602 --> 00:45:31.978
Maybe we could go
to the Hippo Club in 30 minutes?

742
00:45:32.271 --> 00:45:34.898
- Yeah. okay.
- By the way. is this live. or. you know.

743
00:45:34.982 --> 00:45:37.275
- are we being broadcast again?
- Not right now.

744
00:45:37.568 --> 00:45:40.278
but I tend to record everything
because you never know.

745
00:45:40.446 --> 00:45:42.113
Right. right. That's a good point.

746
00:45:42.197 --> 00:45:43.531
- I'll see you there.
- Okay.

747
00:45:43.782 --> 00:45:47.118
I'd like to explain some things to you
and have a good...

748
00:45:50.080 --> 00:45:52.332
Martin Blank.

749
00:46:02.426 --> 00:46:04.636
- You seem very nervous.
- No. no. I'm not. It's just...

750
00:46:05.971 --> 00:46:07.805
Why do you keep looking over
your shoulder?

751
00:46:07.890 --> 00:46:10.892
No. I just don't like having my back.
you know... It's a habit.

752
00:46:11.018 --> 00:46:13.853
Let's not talk about that.
I want to talk to you.

753
00:46:13.938 --> 00:46:15.355
- Okay.
- Put the spotlight on you.

754
00:46:15.522 --> 00:46:17.607
- Sure.
- You got married.

755
00:46:17.691 --> 00:46:20.652
That's hard to imagine.
It's just unbelievable.

756
00:46:20.736 --> 00:46:23.738
No. it's pretty normal. Martin.
It happens all the time.

757
00:46:23.822 --> 00:46:26.658
It's not like you went away
for the weekend.

758
00:46:27.368 --> 00:46:28.409
Can I ask you a question?

759
00:46:28.494 --> 00:46:31.412
I mean. if it's too personal.
you don't have to answer it.

760
00:46:31.497 --> 00:46:33.039
What happened?

761
00:46:33.666 --> 00:46:35.249
I think...

762
00:46:35.334 --> 00:46:37.835
I think I married him to get away.

763
00:46:38.671 --> 00:46:40.129
Didn't like where I ended up.

764
00:46:40.339 --> 00:46:41.464
What was the guy like?

765
00:46:41.548 --> 00:46:43.925
It doesn't matter.
Just forget about that question.

766
00:46:44.009 --> 00:46:46.469
Same thing happened to me
when I joined the Army.

767
00:46:46.553 --> 00:46:50.640
- It's a marriage of sorts.
- On prom night. That's psychotic.

768
00:46:51.934 --> 00:46:54.811
How could you possibly
join the Army?

769
00:46:54.895 --> 00:46:58.564
It's something I felt I had to do.
I know it doesn't make any sense.

770
00:46:58.649 --> 00:47:00.066
No. it doesn't make any sense.

771
00:47:00.359 --> 00:47:03.736
Do you know how much time I spent on
this masochistic cycle just trying

772
00:47:03.821 --> 00:47:06.197
- to figure out what I'd done?
- Nothing.

773
00:47:06.323 --> 00:47:08.866
Yeah. well. you tell me that now.
A little late.

774
00:47:09.201 --> 00:47:12.078
And I thought you'd been murdered
or brainwashed or...

775
00:47:12.329 --> 00:47:13.955
At least I'd hoped that's what happened.

776
00:47:14.039 --> 00:47:16.082
Sorry to disappoint you.

777
00:47:16.166 --> 00:47:19.877
So. you know. come on. spill.
What you been doing the last 10 years?

778
00:47:20.170 --> 00:47:22.922
Well. you must have experiences
you wanna tell me about.

779
00:47:23.007 --> 00:47:25.049
- Bad experiences.
- You've met people?

780
00:47:25.259 --> 00:47:28.511
- Bad people.
- You're pathetic. Know what you need?

781
00:47:28.595 --> 00:47:30.430
- What?
- Shockabuku.

782
00:47:30.514 --> 00:47:32.223
You wanna tell me what that means?

783
00:47:32.307 --> 00:47:36.394
It's a swift. spiritual kick to the head
that alters your reality forever.

784
00:47:37.396 --> 00:47:38.896
That'd be good.

785
00:47:39.064 --> 00:47:40.815
I think.

786
00:47:41.900 --> 00:47:44.736
Listen. I could pick you
up for the reunion around 7:00.

787
00:47:44.945 --> 00:47:48.114
Wait a minute. Let me get this straight.
You are asking me

788
00:47:48.282 --> 00:47:52.118
- to go as your date to the reunion?
- Yes.

789
00:47:53.078 --> 00:47:56.122
- It's unbelievable.
- Well. you know. what the hell?

790
00:47:56.290 --> 00:47:58.624
- I'm not even planning on going.
- Really?

791
00:47:58.709 --> 00:48:02.962
Really. I'm... I was just gonna be mean
about them on the radio. You know?

792
00:48:03.088 --> 00:48:05.506
- Yeah. yeah.
- Besides. it's gonna be depressing.

793
00:48:05.591 --> 00:48:09.010
Maybe. But listen. if you wanna go.
I can't think of any reason

794
00:48:09.094 --> 00:48:11.387
- why we wouldn't go together.
- I can.

795
00:48:11.472 --> 00:48:13.514
I think you can open up. forgive a little.

796
00:48:13.766 --> 00:48:16.017
I think it'd be good for you.
I'll be on time.

797
00:48:16.101 --> 00:48:18.561
Showing up would be a big step.

798
00:48:21.482 --> 00:48:23.357
- Well. I'll think about it.
- Really?

799
00:48:23.442 --> 00:48:26.319
- Yeah.
- Oh. my God. It's Marvin and Debi.

800
00:48:26.570 --> 00:48:28.613
It's me. Amy.

801
00:48:28.781 --> 00:48:30.364
- Amy.
- Yes.

802
00:48:30.449 --> 00:48:31.824
You're still together?

803
00:48:32.284 --> 00:48:35.828
Oh. God. you were the coolest couple.

804
00:48:37.247 --> 00:48:38.706
Still are. I am so sorry.

805
00:48:38.957 --> 00:48:41.209
- That's okay. No. God.
- Here. Want my drink?

806
00:48:41.293 --> 00:48:44.295
- Don't worry about a thing.
- Debi. I love your show.

807
00:48:44.421 --> 00:48:47.048
- It's so timeless.
- Yeah. it does run a little long.

808
00:48:47.132 --> 00:48:49.842
- Marvin. are you here for the reunion?
- Sure.

809
00:48:49.927 --> 00:48:52.720
- Where you been these last 10 years?
- Yeah. Marv. where you been?

810
00:48:52.805 --> 00:48:54.180
You look great.

811
00:48:54.681 --> 00:48:57.058
- I work at Kentucky Fried Chicken.
- You do not.

812
00:48:57.142 --> 00:48:59.769
I do. I sell biscuits and gravy
all over the southland.

813
00:49:00.646 --> 00:49:02.313
You're so funny. He's a funny guy.

814
00:49:03.315 --> 00:49:04.857
You know Tim. my husband?

815
00:49:05.109 --> 00:49:07.693
Why don't I get you another
drink and you can catch up?

816
00:49:07.778 --> 00:49:09.987
Could I have a Stoli with three olives
and an onion?

817
00:49:10.280 --> 00:49:12.240
- Yeah.
- I'll have what she's having.

818
00:49:12.324 --> 00:49:13.908
Sure.

819
00:49:18.997 --> 00:49:20.998
Hi.

820
00:49:26.839 --> 00:49:30.299
Girl down there.
she doesn't trust me anymore.

821
00:49:30.384 --> 00:49:32.093
I don't know why.

822
00:49:32.177 --> 00:49:34.011
I'm trying to earn back her trust.

823
00:49:42.521 --> 00:49:44.856
I'm gonna go finish my drink.
walk her to the car.

824
00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:47.441
I'll be at the hotel in a half hour.

825
00:49:47.526 --> 00:49:49.360
I'll see you there?

826
00:49:54.366 --> 00:49:57.451
- That's him.
- Yeah. we know. thank you.

827
00:49:57.536 --> 00:49:59.245
We've been following him around.

828
00:49:59.329 --> 00:50:00.955
What's the problem here?
You guys on an hourly rate?

829
00:50:01.540 --> 00:50:03.833
If we observe the subject
in an illegal act.

830
00:50:03.917 --> 00:50:07.003
only then can we intervene
and terminate.

831
00:50:07.087 --> 00:50:08.171
Yeah.

832
00:50:08.380 --> 00:50:10.756
Why don't you just go
and shoot the fucker. huh?

833
00:50:10.841 --> 00:50:13.759
Because we are not assassins.
Mr. Grocer.

834
00:50:14.011 --> 00:50:16.888
- We work for the American government.
- Hey. he's coming back.

835
00:50:19.892 --> 00:50:22.268
He's not coming back.

836
00:50:25.397 --> 00:50:27.857
Fuck you guys.

837
00:50:28.442 --> 00:50:31.110
Hey. I don't appreciate being hosed.

838
00:50:32.237 --> 00:50:33.863
You're exactly the same.

839
00:50:33.947 --> 00:50:35.114
So are you.

840
00:50:35.199 --> 00:50:37.783
- I am? How so?
- Just like I remembered you.

841
00:50:37.868 --> 00:50:39.785
Yeah? Troubled?

842
00:50:39.912 --> 00:50:42.914
I'm troubled? Yeah. I got...
I got a few problems. Don't you?

843
00:50:43.081 --> 00:50:44.665
- Sure.
- Yeah? What'd you do?

844
00:50:44.750 --> 00:50:46.417
I tried everything. you know.

845
00:50:46.501 --> 00:50:49.337
I went to the nutritionist. the herbalist.
the psychiatrist.

846
00:50:49.421 --> 00:50:53.716
- That's quite a list. Any of it work?
- I can't tell. but you gotta try. you know?

847
00:50:53.800 --> 00:50:56.052
- It's your duty.
- Yeah. patriot. sure. sure.

848
00:50:56.136 --> 00:50:58.971
- Yeah.
- So tell me more about your problems.

849
00:50:59.056 --> 00:51:02.642
And I'll tell you about mine
and then we'll solve them tonight.

850
00:51:03.977 --> 00:51:05.686
Not so fast.

851
00:51:05.771 --> 00:51:09.106
- You're still in the penalty box.
- Right. right. right.

852
00:51:10.776 --> 00:51:13.069
Well. thanks for coming to see me.

853
00:51:14.112 --> 00:51:17.615
- So is there a Mrs. Mysterio?
- No. but I have a very nice cat.

854
00:51:17.699 --> 00:51:19.408
- Not the same.
- You don't know my cat.

855
00:51:19.493 --> 00:51:20.868
It's very demanding.

856
00:51:20.953 --> 00:51:24.413
- It? You don't know if it's a boy or a girl?
- I respect its privacy.

857
00:51:27.459 --> 00:51:29.585
- Are you happy?
- Kind of.

858
00:51:29.670 --> 00:51:31.963
- Really?
- Sort of.

859
00:51:32.631 --> 00:51:33.839
We'll talk soon?

860
00:51:34.091 --> 00:51:35.633
Okay.

861
00:51:40.305 --> 00:51:42.640
That's a nice ride.
Nobody buys American anymore. huh?

862
00:52:00.492 --> 00:52:01.826
- Hello.
- Marcella. what do you got?

863
00:52:01.910 --> 00:52:04.537
Hey. that town is hot.

864
00:52:04.621 --> 00:52:07.081
I got the stink from
an assistant over at Rothschild's.

865
00:52:07.165 --> 00:52:08.165
We prepped together.

866
00:52:08.250 --> 00:52:10.710
I downloaded everything.
so just call it up.

867
00:52:10.794 --> 00:52:12.503
I'm online.

868
00:52:14.631 --> 00:52:18.843
We've got Steven Lardner. a.k.a. Steve.

869
00:52:19.011 --> 00:52:21.679
and Kenneth McCullers.
no pseudonym.

870
00:52:21.763 --> 00:52:24.265
Steve was a red-shirt tailback
from Ohio State.

871
00:52:24.349 --> 00:52:27.476
McCullers. all-American wrestler
from Northwestern.

872
00:52:27.561 --> 00:52:29.979
- MBA from the same.
- What are they doing here?

873
00:52:30.063 --> 00:52:32.898
Well. they're domestic
covert operatives for the NSA.

874
00:52:32.983 --> 00:52:36.527
up there as part of
a new get-tough-on-terror campaign.

875
00:52:36.653 --> 00:52:39.739
They're looking for an Oswald.
a patsy to take the fall.

876
00:52:39.823 --> 00:52:42.116
- Grocer fed them you.
- Grocer set me up?

877
00:52:42.200 --> 00:52:43.701
- Surprised?
- No.

878
00:52:44.036 --> 00:52:45.453
They were supposed to
catch you in the act.

879
00:52:45.537 --> 00:52:47.955
but I guess they weren't
quick enough. right?

880
00:52:49.374 --> 00:52:53.085
- Who's the ghoul?
- Well. this guy is a badass.

881
00:52:53.253 --> 00:52:55.629
Felix La Poubelle.

882
00:52:55.714 --> 00:52:58.966
An accomplished amateur
with the Basque Nationalists.

883
00:52:59.051 --> 00:53:01.594
A few odd jobs
with the Algerian separatists.

884
00:53:01.762 --> 00:53:06.140
Went pro with a stunning debut
aboard an elite Caribbean cruise liner.

885
00:53:06.224 --> 00:53:08.267
That's where I know him from.
He's an asshole.

886
00:53:08.352 --> 00:53:10.144
Did loan-outs for LikkenBakken.

887
00:53:10.228 --> 00:53:14.482
Enjoys Native American art.
ballroom dancing. pornography...

888
00:53:14.566 --> 00:53:16.192
Yeah. yeah. yeah. What is he here for?

889
00:53:16.276 --> 00:53:19.695
It's part of that Oregon snafu
with that dog. Budro.

890
00:53:19.780 --> 00:53:23.032
You're gonna get out of there. right?
That's not right. You gotta get out.

891
00:53:23.283 --> 00:53:26.077
- You're on a flight tonight. right?
- It isn't done.

892
00:53:27.329 --> 00:53:28.496
This is not good.

893
00:53:29.331 --> 00:53:30.664
I'll do it tomorrow. it's fine.

894
00:53:30.749 --> 00:53:32.708
Sir. I'm beginning to
worry about your safety.

895
00:53:32.959 --> 00:53:34.085
Look. I have to go.

896
00:53:34.211 --> 00:53:37.171
Yeah. we all have to go sometime. sir.
but we can choose when.

897
00:53:37.547 --> 00:53:39.799
No one chooses when.

898
00:55:06.386 --> 00:55:08.179
You can't come in.

899
00:55:08.263 --> 00:55:12.475
Well. I was in the neighborhood.
so I just stopped by.

900
00:55:12.559 --> 00:55:13.934
Wanted to say hi. Can I come in?

901
00:55:15.020 --> 00:55:19.440
You can come in. but only for a second.

902
00:55:30.243 --> 00:55:31.327
Unbelievable.

903
00:55:32.829 --> 00:55:34.663
It's exactly the same.

904
00:55:34.831 --> 00:55:37.666
It's a shrine. It's only temporary.

905
00:55:38.251 --> 00:55:40.336
My apartment burned down
on Devil's Night.

906
00:55:40.712 --> 00:55:42.379
Really.

907
00:55:43.173 --> 00:55:44.965
So you never gave me an answer.

908
00:55:45.050 --> 00:55:47.968
- I said we'd talk later.
- Well. this is later.

909
00:55:48.053 --> 00:55:49.637
See. I figure if we go together.

910
00:55:49.721 --> 00:55:51.555
we have a better chance
of getting out alive.

911
00:55:51.890 --> 00:55:55.893
You know. we can partner up.
watch for traps. you know. go tandem.

912
00:55:56.061 --> 00:55:57.811
I think it'd be a lot safer
than if we lone-wolfed it.

913
00:55:58.563 --> 00:56:01.690
I have to say I'm curious
as to what 10 years has done to you.

914
00:56:01.775 --> 00:56:02.900
You. too.

915
00:56:04.110 --> 00:56:05.528
Is...

916
00:56:06.863 --> 00:56:07.947
Is that the same bed?

917
00:56:08.323 --> 00:56:09.323
Uh huh.

918
00:56:10.283 --> 00:56:12.117
The magic bed.

919
00:56:12.911 --> 00:56:15.246
The magic carpet. Wow.

920
00:56:18.291 --> 00:56:21.168
I'll tell you what. I'll give you an answer
if you give me an airplane.

921
00:56:21.586 --> 00:56:23.671
- Okay.
- Cool.

922
00:56:25.131 --> 00:56:27.758
- Ready?
- Okay.

923
00:56:28.927 --> 00:56:30.928
- Keep your feet low.
- I remember.

924
00:56:31.012 --> 00:56:33.097
It's been 10 years.

925
00:56:33.890 --> 00:56:35.933
- Fly. be free. be free.
- I'm flying.

926
00:56:36.017 --> 00:56:37.184
Emancipation.

927
00:56:37.269 --> 00:56:39.562
- Are you free?
- Of course. Okay.

928
00:56:39.646 --> 00:56:41.730
- What if your dad comes in?
- You can give him one. too.

929
00:56:42.732 --> 00:56:45.317
Okay. You can pick me up at 7:00.

930
00:56:46.278 --> 00:56:49.363
Put me down. You can pick me up.

931
00:56:54.786 --> 00:56:56.745
Okay. you can go now.

932
00:56:57.038 --> 00:56:58.581
You want me to leave right now.

933
00:56:58.665 --> 00:57:01.542
You don't wanna. maybe. watch CNN.
Crossfire. something romantic?

934
00:57:01.626 --> 00:57:06.088
- No. airplane was quite enough.
- Okay. I'll go. That's fine. I'll go.

935
00:57:06.464 --> 00:57:07.965
But this night. tomorrow night.

936
00:57:08.049 --> 00:57:11.635
the reunion is gonna be
an important step

937
00:57:12.095 --> 00:57:15.431
in our. you know.
burgeoning relationship.

938
00:57:15.807 --> 00:57:17.766
You're a fucking psycho.

939
00:57:17.851 --> 00:57:20.769
Don't rush to judgment
on something like that

940
00:57:20.854 --> 00:57:22.605
until all the facts are in.

941
00:57:22.981 --> 00:57:25.149
- I'll just let myself out.
- Go.

942
00:57:26.151 --> 00:57:28.652
And. you can. you know.
lock the door behind me.

943
00:57:28.778 --> 00:57:31.405
because. you know.
a lot of undesirables around.

944
00:57:31.489 --> 00:57:33.907
I'll call you. I'll go.

945
00:57:44.169 --> 00:57:45.586
Oh. shit. there he is.

946
00:57:50.383 --> 00:57:53.177
Man. why don't we just do his job
so we can do our job

947
00:57:53.303 --> 00:57:54.637
and get the fuck out of here?

948
00:57:55.180 --> 00:57:57.222
What do you mean do his job?

949
00:57:57.307 --> 00:57:59.433
What am I. a cold-blooded killer?
I'm not a cold-blooded killer.

950
00:57:59.517 --> 00:58:01.935
- Now. wait a minute...
- No. you wait a minute.

951
00:58:02.896 --> 00:58:05.689
You wanna kill the good guy.
but not be the bad guy.

952
00:58:05.774 --> 00:58:09.943
Doesn't work like that. You gotta wait
until the bad guy kills the good guy.

953
